title: title1
message: Everyone knows that debugging is twice as hard as writing a program in the first place. So if you're as clever as you can be when you write it, how will you ever debug it?

title: title2
message: Some of the best programming is done on paper, really. Putting it into the computer is just a minor detail.

title: title3
message: When you don't create things, you become defined by your tastes rather than ability. Your tastes only narrow & exclude people. So create.

title: title4
message: I'm not a great programmer; I'm just a good programmer with great habits.

title: title5
message: Walking on water and developing software from a specification are easy if both are frozen.

title: title6
message: The most disastrous thing that you can ever learn is your first programming language.

title: title7
message: The most important property of a program is whether it accomplishes the intention of its user.

title: title8
message: Delivering good software today is often better than perfect software tomorrow, so finish things and ship.

title: title9
message: If you optimize everything, you will always be unhappy.

title: title10
message: It's not a bug; it's an undocumented feature.
